    <bioghist>Johnson served in Company F, 6th Michigan Infantry and Heavy Artillery, during the Civil War. After the war he lived in Lansing, Mich.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Letters written to relatives describing his military experience, chiefly in Louisiana and Alabama. He describes the siege of Port Hudson, and one letter includes a sketch map of the lower Mississippi Valley. The collection also includes other family correspondence.</scopecontent>
